The paper proposes a design flow for accelerating neural networks in embedded FPGAs, which falls under the category of hardware design for neural networks. The focus is on low latency and low energy consumption, which suggests a focus on embedded systems and edge computing. The paper also discusses network training and deployment, which suggests a focus on machine learning. Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.ET (Embedded Systems), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.EM (Emerging Technologies).
